com.neebal.android.simplyreliable

Class SimplyReliableInfra

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.SimplyReliableInfra

  • public class SimplyReliableInfra
extends Object
    Class responsible for setting up the infrastructure and initialization required by the SimplyReliable API. This class provides a singleton instance that can be used throughout an application to interact with the SimplyReliable API infrastructure. Some of the common interactions include building new messages, sending messages to the queues, setting the custom http headers that will be sent in every request to the server.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Neebal Technologies

      • init

        public static SimplyReliableInfra init(String rootUrl,
                       HashMap<String,String> customHeaders,
                       Context appContext)
        Initialize the SimplyReliableInfra instance on the basis of the passed rootUrl (does not include the resource path of it). This method is responsible to initialize the infrastructure of the SimplyReliable api.

        Note : Multiple calls to this method, will not result in the infrastructure getting re initialized, as you are playing with a singleton instance here
        Parameters:
        rootUrl - the url that will be used to connect with the server. This is the root url as it does not include the resources that need to be called. The root url should be without the trailing slash. The rest of the resource path of the url will be automatically generated based on the message type.
        customHeaders - application specific custom http headers that need to be sent to the server
        appContext - Android Application context instance
        Returns:
        the SimplyReliableInfra singleton instance.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the context object passed is null

      • getInstance

        public static SimplyReliableInfra getInstance()
        Returns:
        the singleton instance of the SimplyReliableInfra class.

        Note : Before calling this method, make sure that the init() has been called.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if this method is called before calling the init()

        public OutMessage createPostOutMessage(Resource resourcePath,
                              Serializable messageBody,
                              Type responseType)
        Create a PostMessage instance using the various parameters passed

        Note: This method will create a PostMessage instance that is synchronous in nature
        Parameters:
        resourcePath - the Resource path where the REST request needs to be sent to. The rooturl along with this resourcePath will build the entire URL of the request that needs to be sent to the server
        messageBody - the body containing the data of the new resource that needs to be created
        responseType - a response Type instance representing the entire response structure that is expected out of this post request.
        e.g. Type responseType = new TypeToken<Foo<Bar>>() {}.getType(); if we expect the json response to be unmarshalled back to the class Foo<Bar>
        Returns:
        the newly created PostMessage instance
